In the Matter of William M. Hannafin, Appellant. Committee on Character and Fitness of the Second Judicial Department, Respondent. Submitted September 28, 1964; decided October 1, 1964. William M. Hannafin, pro se, for motion.

No one opposed.

*962Motion dismissed upon the ground that the order sought to be appealed from does not finally determine the proceeding within the meaning of the Constitution, without prejudice, however, to a new application for admission if the applicant be so advised (see Matter of Weiss, 13 N Y 2d 897).
